The paper proposes a novel learning-based approach for point cloud completion, which involves generating missing regions in 3D point clouds. This task is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR) as it involves processing and manipulating 3D data. The proposed method also utilizes multi-scale generating networks and adversarial loss, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE).
